							<a name="Vacation Updates">Vacation Updates
					</td>
					<td align="right">
						<font face="verdana" color="#6B5A39" size="-2">
						Tuesday, February&nbsp;20
					</td>
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<font face="verdana" color="#BFBFBF" size="-1">
						<div align="justify">
							Voting has been closed after 10 days of waiting around!
					Congratulations to Malcore as our newest
					member!<br><br>

					The Current Riddle of the week has been up there for more than a
					couple weeks! Lets see if we can get someone to solve this one,
					and Boisvert says it is easy!<br><br>
					
					Rules for apply and voting have been slightly modifyed. To apply
					to The Hidden one must send an email to the follow <a
					href="mailto:Boisvert@Innoruuk.com;charon86@hotmail.com?Subject=
					Application to The Hidden">addresses</a>. The application will
					then be posted in the Members Only section. Once a Prospective
					Member is sponsored there will be one week of voting. It is
					a Members responsibility to check the forums to see if they need
					to vote. After this week voting shall be closed and votes
					counted.<br><br>
					
					All Members should check the <a
					href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fhiddenfrm0">General</a> Forum to
					give their input on looting rules.<br><br>

					All Members should check the <a
					href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fhiddenfrm3">Members Only</a>
					Forum to give their input on recruiting.<br><br>

					An invasion is in the works for Weds night. Keep tuned in so you
					can make it!<bR><bR>

					Malcore will need help on Thursday evening at 11pm EST to kill a
					mob in the Temple of Solusek Ro for his epic quest! The more the
					merrier!<bR><br>

					Our customary Saturday invasion needs a destination, time to
					start thinking where you want to go!
							<br>~ <a href="mailto:Boisvertbladesong@hotmail.com">Boisvert</a><br><br>
							<center><hr size="1" color="#6B5A39" width="200"><center>
						</div>
					</td>
