					<td align="left">
						<font face="verdana" color="#6B5A39" size="+1">
							<a name="Trakanon's Teeth">Trakanon's Teeth
					</td>
					<td align="right">
						<font face="verdana" color="#6B5A39" size="-2">
						Monday, February&nbsp;12
					</td>
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2">
						<font face="verdana" color="#BFBFBF" size="-1">
						<div align="justify">
							Saturday evening the 10th The Hidden and friends arrived in
					Trakanon's Teeth. After a late start we started the Forager
					spawn table going. To our dismay we soon found where the Hunter
					was. Doom was up! The scourge of all adventures to Trakanon's
					Teeth. This ghostly Iksar with almost Bard's speed was holding up
					the Hunter Spawn. We gathered up our forces and the battle began.
					Four of our number fell but Doom was himself Doomed and fell to
					the ground blessing us with Pillars of Fire, a 50+ Wizard Spell.

					<br><br>The Hunter was now going and the chase was on! Slowly
					but steadily everyone collected their medallions until we all
					had the parts for a Sebilis key. But before the night was over
					another named showed his face: Crusader Zoglic! Again we prepared
					for the fight and he charged our ranks. Boisvert took his Harm
					Touch leading him back but survived the whole distance. Zoglic
					was dropped with no casualties. Congrats to Amanar on his new
					Iksar Cerimonial Chestplate!

					<br><br>All members should keep tuned in on the board. There are
					new members waiting for votes. The <a href="roster.asp">Roster</a>
					and the <a href="events.asp">Events</a> page are slowly being
					updated to reflect what is going on. If you have any information
					for either page please email Boisvert at his temporary address:
					<a href="mailto:ug_mug@yahoo.com">ug_mug@yahoo.com</a>
							<br>~ <a href="mailto:Boisvertbladesong@hotmail.com">Boisvert</a><br><br>
							<center><hr size="1" color="#6B5A39" width="200"><center>
						</div>
					</td>
				</tr>
